update timestamp, though that's just within the existing session. Everything else checks out as stable, so the system is operating normally.\n\nWait, I need to reconsider the timing here. The cron session that ran at 12:44 appears to have delivered its output, but I'm not seeing a new Agent Status report come through since 12:34. That's 17 minutes of silence when these reports typically go out every 15 minutes. This could be a timing coincidence since the previous heartbeat was at 12:46 and we're now at 12:51—right in the middle of that window—but it might also signal that the cron isn't firing as expected or the reports aren't reaching the group.\n\nLooking at the pipeline health, nothing's actually changed from the last heartbeat. The Agent Status cron is still running, the zombie session is still there, and all the infrastructure checks are passing. I should stay silent and not send another report. Let me double-check the current session timestamps one more time to make sure I'm not missing anything. Comparing the session states against the last heartbeat, everything's holding steady—no new failures, no fresh blockers, no completed tasks to report. The system remains healthy, so I'm going to stay silent and let the previous report stand.","thinkingSignature":"d60fcbc35fe890bf18222ae4cd3b25a45de7d9c99a36328198aaaa9d638856a2"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state against `heartbeat-state.json` (last check: 12:46 UTC):\n\n**Session comparison:**\n| Session | Last State | Current State | Δ |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `cron:ed2d0b5d` (5p QLHV) | running | running ✅ | stable |\n| `cron:6f3323ef` (5p DTLX) | running | running ✅ | stable |\n| `telegram:group:-5163901258` | running | running ✅ | stable |\n| `telegram:group:-5168104492` | done | done ✅ | stable |\n| `telegram:direct:6053576134` | done | done ✅ | stable |\n| `main` | done | done ✅ | stable |\n| `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) | running (12:34) | running (12:44) ✅ | activity, no new event |\n| `cron:b65